column4: boy I'm getting a lot of "Could not mark all packages for installation or upgrade" errors in Synaptic while following Community Ubuntu Documentations
I must ask... Have you run scripts like Automatix, (NOT recommending that you do.) to install anything?
No I've not, last time I did, it crashed webpages with flash content. I started from scratch using the Ubuntu Community Documentation and I simply can't install the packages it says I should.
Did you do a full reinstall after you tried it ?
Nodnod, full reinstall just this morning, the only other things I've done since the full reinstall was install aiglx+compiz
You might have better luck in that channel.... if all you did was freash install and compiz
You can post your sources.list to the pastebin and I can look at it..
That makes me feel better :) I suppose
Have a great day, Cap'n, and thanks for your attention!
